	(43,2,'2014-12-04 07:21:39','2014-12-04 07:21:39','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">“Please try to remember that what they believe, as well as what they do and cause you to endure does not testify to your inferiority but to their inhumanity\"-</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>James Baldwin The Fire Next Time</strong></p>\r\nShout out to my good friend Catasha Davis who posted this quote on her facebook page moments after the decision had been made to NOT indict the officer,  Daniel Pantaleo who wrongfully killed Eric Garner...\r\n\r\nReading this quote reminded me of the first time I read <em>The Fire Next Time. </em>It was an ironic feeling because the issues that Baldwin was speaking of were written for the people of the 1960\'s...Yet at the time I read it(Fall 2013) I felt as if it were still applicable for today. And  sadly enough, the quote above matches perfectly to the inhumane treatment that certain black bodies have had a history of dealing with and STILL continue to deal with in this present day and age...\r\n\r\nI have made an effort to observe, read, question, analyze, and even ponder all of the different responses about the Mike Brown issue and even the recent Eric Garner decision. It is quite obvious there are number of people who feel beyond hopeless, frustrated beyond measure, and simply just tired…to the point where they want to give up. Perhaps even consider something like this....\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://donteventripp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-41\" src=\"http://donteventripp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/1-300x276.jpg\" alt=\"-1\" width=\"300\" height=\"276\" /></a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\nBut all jokes aside, what I find the most troubling are the people who are apathetic. Or even worse, the ones who refuse to acknowledge the PROBLEM behind this issue. You know the people who want to say things like\r\n\r\n\"Race is not an issue\"\r\n\r\n\"There isn\'t an issue with the police\"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\"The system DOES work\"\r\n\r\nAll of the above statements had me looking...\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://donteventripp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/ew.gif\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-42\" src=\"http://donteventripp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/ew-300x224.gif\" alt=\"ew\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLet\'s get one thing straight. The fact is, what is happening now in 2014 has been happening FOR DECADES! The issue does not just lie with Mike Brown or Eric Garner. Unbeknownst to most people, there has been an ongoing HISTORY of the police showing no type of respect, honor, or value for the lives of black people in this country. The truth of the matter is, the police have been patrolling, killing, and targeting people of color way before you or even I were able to make a facebook opinion about the issue…\r\n\r\nMyself and the rest of the Don’t Even Tripp staff are committed to using our ART to bring awareness, discourse, and informing people of these issues. Don’t Even Tripp’s next production <em>Generation of Dreams</em> highlights this very issue as well brings up the HISTORICAL facts of how what is occurring now has been occurring for decades.\r\n\r\nWe decided to launch the website today <strong>December 4th </strong>because this day holds historical significance in regards to the treatment of black bodies in relation to the police. Today marks the 44th year anniversary of the assignation of Black Panther Leader Fred Hampton.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://donteventripp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Fred_Hampton.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-40 aligncenter\" src=\"http://donteventripp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Fred_Hampton-289x300.png\" alt=\"Fred_Hampton\" width=\"289\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nFred Hampton was chairman of the Black Panther Illinois chapter. He rallied  for peace &amp; progression for ALL people and was most recognized for his involvement in the rainbow collation. A movement that prompted Chicago Gangs to end violence and draw peace with one another. Unfortunately Hampton was murdered when the <strong>Chicago police </strong>raided his home while he was sleeping on the night of <strong>December 4th 1969. </strong>The raid was led by FBI Director, J. Edgar Hoover and his task force COINTELPRO. A group dedicated to dismantling peaceful political organizations.\r\n\r\nBu don\'t take my word for it...Do your  own research. Here if you are too lazy to do the research let me provide you with some helpful articles:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.democracynow.org/2009/12/4/the_assassination_of_fred_hampton_how\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.democracynow.org/<wbr />2009/12/4/the_assassination_<wbr />of_fred_hampton_how</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chicagoreviewpress.com/assassination-of-fred-hampton--the-products-9781556527654.php\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.chicagoreviewpress.<wbr />com/assassination-of-fred-<wbr />hampton--the-products-<wbr />9781556527654.php</a>\r\n\r\nOr if you don’t like to read, here is a film:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NAFyLpvOjyw\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?<wbr />v=NAFyLpvOjyw</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/The-Murder-Fred-Hampton/dp/B000O75GWQ\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.amazon.com/The-<wbr />Murder-Fred-Hampton/dp/<wbr />B000O75GWQ</a>\r\n\r\nBut reading is fundamental\r\n\r\nExcuse my sarcasm on the mannor. My sarcasm is only in attempt to keep my sanity  from the ongoing ignorance I continually see from people who hide behind their computer screens screaming  this issue does not matter. I am no by ways advocating that ALL police are bad. However to not acknoweldge the history, the facts, and issue that there is deep seated attack on is a problem.\r\nRegardless of race, political or social standing, as an active contributing citizen in this society, this issue does matter.\r\n\r\nBlack lives matter, all lives matter.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If you choose not to acknowledge this problem... it is ok because we will. We here at Don’t Even Tripp made a vow that we promise to address, acknowledge, and fully confront social issues like these in our productions.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">So not only STAY TUNED for our next production.... but more importantly</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">STAY INVOLVED, INFORMED, AND ACTIVE!.\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\"They can kill the revoultion but they cannot kill the revolution\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">-Fred Hampton\r\n\r\nDon’t Even Tripp Plans to donate 25% of their ticket proceeds to the Ella Baker Center in Oakland, CA.</p>','D.E.T Supports #BLACKLIVES & The Legacy of Fred Hampton','','inherit','open','open','','39-revision-v1','','','2014-12-04 07:21:39','2014-12-04 07:21:39','',39,'http://donteventripp.com/?p=43',0,'revision','',0),
