	(102,1,'2014-12-04 16:27:58','2014-12-04 16:27:58','Tells the story of a young man dealing with th murder of his younger sister. He claims he has found peace through God but is masking his pain with an addiction to pain killers. The play addressed social issues of teen trafficking, drug addiction, and conflicting religious beliefs.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\nThe production sold out its second night and a total of 240 people from the Bay Area community attended.  D.E.T. partnered up with the non-profit organization Youth Uprising Center and donated half their ticket sales to the organization.</strong>','And An Angel Came Down','','inherit','open','open','','70-revision-v1','','','2014-12-04 16:27:58','2014-12-04 16:27:58','',70,'http://donteventripp.com/?p=102',0,'revision','',0),
