	(70,1,'2014-10-30 21:00:59','2014-10-30 21:00:59','Tells the story of a young man dealing with th murder of his younger sister. He claims he has found peace through God but is masking his pain with an addiction to pain killers. The play addressed social issues of teen trafficking, drug addiction, and conflicting religious beliefs.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\nThe production sold out its second night and a total of 240 people from the Bay Area community attended.  D.E.T. partnered up with the non-profit organization Youth Uprising Center and donated half their ticket sales to the organization.</strong>','And An Angel Came Down','','publish','closed','closed','','and-an-angel-came-down','','','2014-12-04 16:27:58','2014-12-04 16:27:58','',0,'http://detp.boom/?post_type=project&#038;p=70',0,'project','',0),
	(78,1,'2014-11-07 20:32:35','2014-11-07 20:32:35','Ayasha is from Pittsburg, CA and has been a lover of theatre and storytelling since the age of 7. She Received her B.S. in Film &amp; New Media from San Diego State University - during her undergraduate experience she studiend abroad to Singapore - attending Nanyang Technological University in the Theater &amp; Communications department. A few years after college, Ayasha decided to  M.A. in Afro-American Studies from the University of Wisconsin-Madison and studied Theatre/Communication Studies at in Singapore. She has had the opportunity to teach theatre and writing at the University of Wisconsin Madison and UC Berkeley’s Upward Bound Program. She has directed short films <i>Unidentified </i>and <i>Bowling from Behind. </i> She also has written/directed two full length plays: <i>The Skin I’m in(Spring 2008) </i> and <i>And an Angel Came Down</i>(Spring 2010) She is passionate about helping her community and aims to assist others in discovering their power and purpose through arts and education.','Ayasha Tripp','Ayasha is from Pittsburg, CA and has been a lover of theatre and storytelling since the age of 7. She Received her B.S. in Film & New Media from San Diego State University - during her undergraduate experience she studiend abroad to Singapore - attending Nanyang Technological University in the Theater & Communications department.','publish','closed','closed','','ayasha-tripp','','','2014-11-07 20:32:35','2014-11-07 20:32:35','',0,'http://detp.boom/?post_type=team&amp;p=78',0,'team','',0),
	(81,1,'2014-11-07 20:34:00','2014-11-07 20:34:00','','Asia Jackson','','publish','closed','closed','','asia-jackson','','','2014-11-07 20:34:00','2014-11-07 20:34:00','',0,'http://detp.boom/?post_type=team&amp;p=81',1,'team','',0),
	(83,1,'2014-11-07 20:34:48','2014-11-07 20:34:48','Arielle hails from Oakland, CA and usually won’t shy away from making this fact known. She is very proud of the diverse melting pot of family genes that have come together to make her who she is today. Along with the rest of the DET team, Arielle earned her Bachelors degree from San Diego State University, majoring in Public Relations with a minor in Sociology. She has used her skills from SDSU in a range professional settings, but prefers her place in the space of planning, creativity, helping others, and kids, and has been blessed with a 3 year old of her own! Arielle has just begun a new journey as teacher with Music Together, an international early childhood music and movement program. In Fall 2015, she also plans on beginning a Master of Arts program in Holistic Psychology in order to provide therapy for children and families through expressive arts techniques.\n\n&nbsp;','Arielle Vaughan','','publish','closed','closed','','arielle-vaughan','','','2014-11-07 20:34:48','2014-11-07 20:34:48','',0,'http://detp.boom/?post_type=team&amp;p=83',2,'team','',0),
